Validate must reject duplicate spec IDs, duplicate marker IDs, edges referencing unknown endpoints, self-edges, duplicate edges, or directed cycles among spec-spec edges. Edges whose endpoint does not exist (broken edges — typically a typo in a &lt;ref&gt; target) are NOT rejected here; they surface as EDGE_BROKEN events in derived closures so the user can fix the spec text or restore the missing spec. Validation must pass when all references are consistent. See principles.specs_are_truth.